  ;; ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  :section-12-status
  """
  · Doc status: READY.
  · Awaits: Alfred read + GO on Cycle A.
  · Prior doctrine preserved: CORPUS-PROPORTIONAL-LIMA-METHODOLOGY-
    2026-07-17.ENG.slat remains authoritative for the reveal-and-
    rebalance frame. This doc EXTENDS it with the full polish
    pipeline and cross-model transfer.
  · No commits until Alfred says commit.
  · No fires until Alfred says fire.
  """
)

;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
;; § SECTION 13 — MANDATORY PRE-FIRE PREFLIGHT (added 2026-07-19)
;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
;;
;; Added post-Mk-1-first-crash on 2026-07-19. The Grand Weave produces
;; a fold; the fold produces a corpus; before that corpus enters Forge,
;; it MUST pass a preflight check. Two failures on Mk 1's first fire
;; proved this rule with real evidence.
;;
;; Failure 1 — empty pairs in the corpus:
;;   mlx_lm loads a batch, some pairs have empty content, gradient is
;;   computed over an empty batch → `ValueError: [grad] Must specify at
;;   least one argument`. 30 seconds in, training dies. Mk 1's first
;;   fire crashed here — 40 empty pairs from the v8 base corpus.
;;
;; Failure 2 — huge pairs (over max_seq_length):
;;   Book chapters up to 122k chars silently truncated by mlx_lm's
;;   4,096-token limit. If truncation removes the whole assistant reply,
;;   the effective content is empty and the run dies with the same
;;   grad error. Mk 1's second fire crashed here — 269 book-chapter
;;   pairs, some > 100k chars each.
;;
;; The preflight rule (mandatory, non-negotiable, added to Weave):
;;
;;   1. Every JSONL row must parse as valid JSON.
;;   2. Every row must have a `messages` field with ≥ 2 entries.
;;   3. Both user and assistant content must be non-empty (stripped).
;;   4. Combined (user + assistant) length must not exceed ~12,000 chars
;;      (safe headroom under a 4,096-token max_seq_length ≈ 16k chars).
;;   5. Assistant content must be ≥ 5 chars.
;;
;; Failure of ANY of these = do not fire. Filter corpus, re-preflight,
;; then fire.
;;
;; Reference implementation:
;;   ~/code/motoi-scheme/scripts/corpus-preflight.py
;;
;; Reference runbook (with rubric per step):
;;   ~/code/motoi-scheme/engineering/RUNBOOK-CORPUS-FOLD-MEASUREMENT-2026-07-19.ENG.slat
;;
;; Reference SRE Manual chapter (full runbook):
;;   ~/code/motoi-scheme/SRE-MANUAL/chapters/01-forge-preflight-and-fire.slat
;;
;; This preflight is Step 3.5 of the corpus-fold-measurement runbook.
;; It runs after the fold produces JSONL and before forge-fire.sh is
;; called. Never fire without a passing preflight. The check is cheap
;; (one linear pass over the corpus). The crash it prevents is 5+
;; minutes of Forge spinup + confusion.
;;
;; SECTION 13 CROSS-REFERENCE:
;;
;;   Where preflight lives              What it protects
;;   ──────────────────────────────    ───────────────────────────────────
;;   scripts/corpus-preflight.py       Empty + malformed + huge + short pairs
;;   forge-fire.sh (wrap it)           mlx_lm grad-empty-batch crash
;;   SRE-MANUAL/chapters/01-forge…     Full runbook with 10 sections
;;   RUNBOOK-CORPUS-FOLD-MEASUREMENT   Step 3.5 with pass/fail rubric

;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
;; § SECTION 14 — Reading training curves as data signals (added 2026-07-19)
;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
;;
;; The Grand Weave's loss curves during training are not just numbers —
;; they are the data speaking about itself. Different iter ranges give
;; different signals. Full runbook with iter-by-iter rubric:
;;
;;   ~/code/motoi-scheme/SRE-MANUAL/chapters/02-training-signals-and-data.slat
;;
;; Twelve sections covering:
;;   § 2 iter 1           — cold-start distance from base
;;   § 3 iters 10–100    — is data learnable at all
;;   § 4 iters 200–2000  — shape of corpus (steep vs plateau)
;;   § 5 train vs val   — generalization signal
;;   § 6 save_every ck  — probe protocol (real data question)
;;   § 7 end of epoch 1 — what actually stuck
;;   § 8 epoch 2 delta  — corpus density
;;   § 9 LR + loss      — learning efficiency
;;   § 10 cross-gen     — trajectory comparison against Mk B
;;   § 11 quick-ref     — action table by iter range
;;   § 12 the override  — probes are ground truth, curves are proxy
;;
;; Every threshold anchored to real Mk A / Mk B / Mk 1 measurements.
;; Update chapter 02 whenever a new Mk reveal lands.

;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
;; § SECTION 15 — MK 2 CPT INTEGRATION INTO FORGE (added 2026-07-21)
;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
;;
;; Landed 2026-07-21 by Alfred + Claude direct edits (no sub-agents).
;; The CPT pipeline is now a first-class citizen of Forge.
;;
;; UI ── /cpt page (new):
;;   · web/templates/cpt.html
;;   · web/static/cpt.css
;;   · web/static/cpt.js
;;   · Status cards + config panel + data-mix bars + fire button + console
;;   · Mobile-friendly (topbar wraps at <720px, colors preserved)
;;
;; Backend API (all in web/server.py):
;;   GET  /api/cpt/status       → stream info + active-run info
;;   POST /api/cpt/preflight    → runs scripts/cpt-prep/preflight.py
;;   POST /api/cpt/fire         → refuses if preflight FAIL; else fires
;;   GET  /api/cpt/lacan-status → Lacan Kit demo state
;;   POST /api/cpt/lacan-demo   → regenerates 25-node Lacan demo
;;   GET  /lacan-demo           → renders demo MD as HTML
;;
;; Fire script:
;;   scripts/forge-fire-cpt.sh  (sibling of forge-fire.sh)
;;   · Same sidecar discipline: writes pid, train.cfg symlink,
;;     resume-offset.json, banner line
;;   · Warns if config isn't fine_tune_type: full
;;   · Warns if data dir lacks text-format JSONL
;;
;; Removed:
;;   Chat-with-LLM feature (forge-chat.js/css/html) — Lacuna owns that
;;   role. Nav entry removed 2026-07-21. Backend route left in place
;;   for cleanup later.
;;
;; Lacan Paraphrase Kit (~/code/forge/forge/lacan/):
;;   · Deterministic surface-form variety (metaphor via WordNet +
;;     metonymy via spaCy + 5 field-rotation templates + voice)
;;   · Kept in Forge because it composes with the training toolkit
;;   · NOT applied to Mk 2 CPT stream (deferred to Mk 2.1 if
;;     measurement shows Tier 1 attachment thin)
;;   · Full doctrine: memory/project_lacan_paraphrase_kit_2026_07_21
;;   · Full report: engineering/LACAN-KIT-DEMO-2026-07-21.md

;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
;; § SECTION 16 — MK 2 CPT EXECUTION DECISIONS + REASONING (2026-07-21)
;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
;;
;; Fired 2026-07-21T09:02:53Z. Mac Studio M2 Max 32GB. PID 81884.
;;
;; Full reasoning trail lives at:
;;   SRE-MANUAL/chapters/05-*.slat § section-cpt-execution-decisions-2026-07-21
;;
;; Summary of decisions + WHY:
;;
;;   1. fine_tune_type: full  (NOT LoRA)
;;      · Physics-3.1 requires full-weight updates for knowledge injection
;;      · LoRA is task-adaptation only (Mk 1 mode)
;;      · 748.765M / 1.54B trainable (48.5%, output emb tied)
;;      · Fits in 32GB with bf16 + fp32 Adam (peak ~9-13GB)
;;
;;   2. bf16 weights + fp32 Adam optimizer states
;;      · bf16: native on M-series, 2× mem savings, stable
;;      · fp32 Adam: bulletproof, no quantization noise
;;      · 8-bit Adam considered but not needed (had headroom)
;;      · Full doctrine: memory/reference_bf16_vs_8bit_adam_cpt_config_2026_07_21
;;
;;   3. learning_rate: 1.0e-5 with cosine decay to 1e-6
;;      · CPT wants gentle updates (SFT can handle 1e-4)
;;      · Qwen team recommends 5e-5 to 1e-4 — we're conservative
;;      · 5% warmup (971 of 19,413 steps)
;;      · Room to bump to 3e-5 in Mk 2.5 if val loss barely moves
;;
;;   4. iters: 19,413 (1 epoch at effective batch 4)
;;      · Physics-3.1's 96.6% result was 1 epoch of augmented data
;;      · Mk 1 LIMO finding: 3 epochs overfits at 1.5B
;;      · Val eval every 500 steps — early stop signal available
;;
;;   5. save_every: 2500 (~8 checkpoints × ~3GB = ~24GB)
;;      · Full CPT saves ALL params — 500-step default would need 120GB
;;      · Still enough insurance (max ~10 min re-train per lost checkpoint)
;;
;;   6. max_seq_length: 1024
;;      · Docs chunked at 512-token blocks during interleave
;;      · Occasional 1146+ truncation (small %, acceptable)
;;      · Long-context progressive scaling deferred to Sakura/later
;;
;;   7. Sequential architecture (7B classifier ≠ concurrent with training)
;;      · 32GB M2 Max can't hold 7B (5GB) + full CPT (18-22GB) simultaneously
;;      · Phase A (classifier) → exit → Phase B (training) → clean
;;      · 7B classifier deferred (only needed for Path B with Lacan ops)
;;
;;   8. NO MeCo cooldown implementation for Mk 2
;;      · MeCo paper (arXiv:2501.01956) prescribes 15% cooldown where
;;        prefix drops from training examples
;;      · Would require custom trainer logic; MLX-LM lora doesn't support
;;      · Deferred to Mk 2.1 — measure first, add if attachment weak
;;
;;   9. NO special-token registration for MeCo prefixes
;;      · Our [axis:X] [tier:N] etc. are regular text
;;      · MeCo paper's mechanism works with text prefixes
;;      · Avoids tokenizer modification (portable across Qwen versions)
;;
;;   10. Qwen native tokens FULLY USED
;;       · <|repo_name|>motoi-scheme<|file_sep|><path> wraps every E + F
;;       · <|fim_prefix|>/<|fim_middle|>/<|fim_suffix|> wraps every G
;;       · Chat template (<|im_start|>/<|im_end|>) untouched (SFT-side)
;;       · Full doctrine: memory/reference_qwen_native_cpt_tokens_2026_07_21
;;
;;   11. Reversed pairs — 5 phrasings per Tier 1 (was 1)
;;       · Reversal Curse (arXiv:2309.12288) requires bidirectional training
;;       · One template repeated 15× (upsample) is NOT the same as 5
;;         distinct phrasings
;;       · Ported from Lacan Kit's reverse_node() → emit_cpt.py directly
;;
;;   12. Tier 1 forward — 5 field-rotation templates (was 1 composite)
;;       · P1 definition-forward · P2 examples-forward · P3 dialogue-
;;         forward · P4 programs-forward · P5 associations-forward
;;       · Each template = a metonymy operation (Lacan syntagmatic axis)
;;       · Voice inflection per axis baked into template choice
;;       · Ported from Lacan Kit's paraphrase_node() → emit_cpt.py directly
;;
;;   Decision NOT made: metaphor axis (WordNet substitution).
;;   Rationale: highest drift risk, would require 7B correction pipeline,
;;   3+ hours of extra compute for ~10% variant lift. Skipped for Mk 2.
;;   Reserved for Mk 2.1 if measurement shows metonymy alone insufficient.

;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
;; § SECTION 17 — SCALING + COST ANALYSIS (2026-07-21)
;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
;;
;; Full details: SRE-MANUAL/chapters/05-*.slat § section-scaling-and-cost-
;; analysis-2026-07-21.
;;
;; WHY 1.5B for Mk 2:
;;   · Proving ground. Doctrine works or doesn't at 1.5B; scale is orthogonal.
;;   · Physics-3.3 capacity: 1.5B ≈ 3 Gbit vs Motoi's <10 Mbit facts.
;;     Not capacity-limited, data-quality-limited.
;;   · Fits comfortably in 32GB M2 Max with full-parameter training.
;;   · Qwen2.5-Coder-1.5B has strong code-adjacent priors — matches Motoi.
;;
;; Compute alternatives evaluated (July 2026 pricing):
;;
;;   OPTION A — Local Mac Studio M2 Max 32GB          [CHOSEN]
;;     Cost: $0/hr. Wall time: 4-8h (thermally derated).
;;     Best for: proving-ground iteration, no vendor deps.
;;
;;   OPTION B — Runpod H100 80GB
;;     Cost: $1.99/hr community · $2.69/hr sxm.
;;     Wall time: 1-2h at 1.5B. Total per run: $4-6.
;;     Best for: SFT after CPT, or 7B/14B base scaling.
;;
;;   OPTION C — Lambda Labs A100 40GB / 80GB
;;     Cost: $1.10/hr (40GB) · $2.00/hr (80GB).
;;     Wall time: 2-3h at 1.5B. Total per run: $3-6.
;;     Best for: managed UI, similar to Runpod.
;;
;;   OPTION D — HuggingFace Inference Endpoints
;;     Not for training. Serving-side only.
;;
;;   OPTION E — Own metal (buy H100 / M3 Ultra Mac Pro)
;;     Long-term commitment. Considered "later" post-Mk-N cadence.
;;
;; WHEN TO GO CLOUD:
;;   · 7B/14B base doesn't fit on 32GB → cloud
;;   · Iteration cadence matters (Mk 2.1/2.2/2.3 rapid) → cloud
;;   · Sakura commercial-scale training → cloud + own metal mix
;;   · Cost tolerance per Alfred: ~$900/major run covers many cloud experiments
;;
;; SCALING PATH:
;;   · Mk 2 (this run)     — 1.5B local, doctrine proving ground
;;   · Mk 2.1 (if needed)  — 1.5B local + Lacan ops + 7B fluency gate
;;   · Mk 3 (potential)    — 7B or 14B, cloud, same doctrine unchanged
;;   · Sakura              — different base + commercial substrate, cloud
;;
;; The doctrine is scale-independent. What changes with scale is
;; compute cost, wall time, and memory budget — NOT the DATA SHAPE we feed.

